# LinkAction (signed `/la`)

CRM signs tokens (ECDSA P-256, private key in `config/keys/`); www verifies and appends JSONL; cron `LBL_LINK_ACTION_IMPORT` fetches via HTTPS API and re-verifies.

**Module-generic:** token payload uses `module`, `record_id`, `email_field` (not module-specific IDs). New modules = registry entry in config + handler class; `LinkActionUrl` / `LinkActionImageUrl` active only for registered modules. Handlers: `CandidatesUnsubscribeHandler`, `CandidatesResubscribeHandler`, `CandidatesOpenHandler` (audit log only). Unsubscribe tokens embed paired `rs_t`; www redirect appends `?rt=` for WordPress resubscribe button.

## Config

- `config/modules/LinkAction.php` — registry, `email_pepper`, `www_base_url`, `queue_api.*`
- Keys gitignored: `config/keys/link_action_private_v1.pem`, `link_action_public_v1.pem`, `link_action_queue_api_key.txt`
- Spec: `documentation/module/LinkAction.md`

## Cyberfolks (itconnect.pl www)

| Item | Value |
|------|--------|
| Public click URL | `https://www.itconnect.pl/la` → `public_html/la.php` |
| Open tracking image | `https://www.itconnect.pl/la/o/{token}/logo.png` → `public_html/img.php` |
| Queue pull API | `https://www.itconnect.pl/la/queue` → `public_html/queue-api.php` |
| Deploy package | `external/www-la/` |

**open_basedir** allows only `public_html` — web PHP cannot read `/home/itconnect/private/`. Runtime data lives in `public_html/_link_action/` (`.htaccess`: `Require all denied`). Config fallback in `Config::load()`: `../private/la/config.php` then `_link_action/config.php`.

Deploy: run `composer install --no-dev` in `external/www-la/`, then rsync (SSH **port 222**):

```bash
REMOTE="itconnect@itconnect.pl:domains/itconnect.pl/public_html"
RSYNC="rsync -avz -e 'ssh -p 222'"
cd external/www-la && composer install --no-dev
eval $RSYNC la.php img.php queue-api.php bootstrap.php "$REMOTE/"
eval $RSYNC vendor/ "$REMOTE/vendor/"
eval $RSYNC src/ "$REMOTE/src/"
eval $RSYNC assets/ "$REMOTE/assets/"
eval $RSYNC responses/ "$REMOTE/responses/"
```

**Agent:** after any `external/www-la/` or LinkAction token/mail change, offer deploy — rsync only what changed when possible; **never** rsync `config.production.php` over live `_link_action/config.php` (merge new keys in place, e.g. `logo_asset_path`). CRM side: ask before running `scripts/sync-freecrm.sh pushsrc`; run new `migrations/LinkAction/` on `test.itconnect.pl` when migrations were added.

**Live host:** `ssh -p 222 itconnect@itconnect.pl` → web root `/home/itconnect/domains/itconnect.pl/public_html/`. Production runs **`bootstrap.php` + `vendor/` + `src/`** (legacy `common.php` may remain unused).

**Config:** edit `public_html/_link_action/config.php` in place — **do not** rsync `config.production.php` (would overwrite `pull_api_key`). Merge new keys (`open`, `logo_asset_path`, `img_rate_limit`, `redirect_url` on Candidates `unsubscribe` → `wypisanie-zakonczone`, `resubscribe` → `zapis-ponowny-do-bazy-mailingowej`) with `__DIR__`-relative paths. Avoid `var_export(require …)` from SSH (CLI cwd breaks paths). Current tracking asset: `assets/pixel.gif` (`logo_asset_path`).

| Path (home-relative) | Purpose |
|---------------------|---------|
| `domains/itconnect.pl/public_html/la.php` | Click endpoint |
| `domains/itconnect.pl/public_html/img.php` | Open-tracking image endpoint |
| `domains/itconnect.pl/public_html/assets/pixel.gif` | 1×1 transparent GIF served by img.php |
| `domains/itconnect.pl/public_html/queue-api.php` | CRM queue pull API |
| `domains/itconnect.pl/public_html/bootstrap.php` + `vendor/` | PSR-4 autoload |
| `domains/itconnect.pl/public_html/src/` | LinkAction www classes (optional on host if only vendor deployed) |
| `domains/itconnect.pl/public_html/_link_action/queue.jsonl` | Queue file |
| `domains/itconnect.pl/public_html/_link_action/keys/link_action_public_v1.pem` | Public key |

Shared secret: `pull_api_key` in www `_link_action/config.php`; CRM reads `config/keys/link_action_queue_api_key.txt` (gitignored) or env `FREECRM_LINK_ACTION_QUEUE_API_KEY`.

Use **`www.itconnect.pl`** in URLs — bare `itconnect.pl` 301s via WordPress.

`.htaccess` in `public_html/` (before WordPress block; **leading `/`** on targets matches live `RewriteBase /`):

```apache
RewriteRule ^la/o/([^/]+)/logo\.png$ /img.php?t=$1 [L,QSA]
RewriteRule ^la/queue$ /queue-api.php [L]
RewriteRule ^la$ /la.php [L,QSA]
```

## WordPress UX (Candidates unsubscribe / resubscribe)

| Step | URL |
|------|-----|
| After unsubscribe click | `wypisanie-zakonczone/?rt=<signed_resubscribe_token>` (Elementor page post **11957**) |
| After resubscribe click | `zapis-ponowny-do-bazy-mailingowej/` |

**Resubscribe button** on `wypisanie-zakonczone`: Elementor Button link = `https://www.itconnect.pl/la?t=` (no shortcodes — Elementor emits them literally). `?rt=` is a **URL query param**, not post meta. Elementor PHP hooks (`before_render`, `render_content`) do **not** change `href` on live (widget/cache); use **Code Snippets** `wp_footer` JS: read `$_GET['rt']`, set `href` on `a.elementor-button[href*="la?t="]` with text „Chcę nadal…”, hide when `rt` empty. Optional `DONOTCACHEPAGE` when `rt` present.

**Live `_link_action/config.php` merge:** `unsubscribe` and `resubscribe` have different `redirect_url` — edit each action block; blind `sed` on the URL string hits both.

## CRM import

- **Pull, not push** — Cyberfolks queues clicks; CRM polls. `vtigercron` runs every minute; `LBL_LINK_ACTION_IMPORT` runs at most once per **300s** → typical latency **1–5 min** after click.
- Cron: `App\Modules\LinkAction\Cron\ImportTask` (300s) — `fetch()` → `importIncoming()` → `ack()`
- Local dirs: `import/link-action/{incoming,processed,failed}/` — must be **writable by `www-data`** (cron runs as `gosu www-data`)
- Manual: `docker compose exec -T cron gosu www-data php cron/vtigercron.php service=LBL_LINK_ACTION_IMPORT`
- **GET `/la/queue`** = read only (queue unchanged). **POST ack** = truncate remote file (after import). Reading queue in browser/curl does not delete it.

## Queue API behaviour

| GET | 200 + JSONL, or 204 empty |
| POST ack | 204; CRM sends `{}` + `Content-Type: application/json` (empty POST blocked by Cyberfolks ModSecurity) |
| Bad key / rate limit | 404 |

WWW logs: `_link_action/pull.log`, `reject.log`, `queue.jsonl`. Inspect via SSH (`ssh -p 222 itconnect@itconnect.pl`).

## Manual smoke

```bash
# 1. Generate URL (saves cache/la_e2e_token.txt)
docker compose exec -T app php -r '…'  # see documentation/module/LinkAction.md

# 2. Click — use @file, NOT @$(cat file)
curl -sS -G "https://www.itconnect.pl/la" --data-urlencode "t@cache/la_e2e_token.txt"

# 2b. Open image (expect image/gif, 1×1 transparent; repeat = replay)
curl -sS -D- -o /tmp/pixel.gif "https://www.itconnect.pl/la/o/{token}/logo.png"

# 3. Peek queue (does not delete)
curl -sS -H "X-LinkAction-Pull-Key: $(cat config/keys/link_action_queue_api_key.txt)" https://www.itconnect.pl/la/queue

# 4. Import + ack
docker compose exec -T cron gosu www-data php cron/vtigercron.php service=LBL_LINK_ACTION_IMPORT
```

Candidates email fields live in `u_yf_candidatescf` (`email_private`, `newsletter_email`); token must match field used at sign time.

## CRM UI

- **Settings → Logs → Link actions** (`Settings:LinkAction` ListView) — read-only audit of `u_yf_link_action_log`; **Mail subject** column joins `mail_message_id` → `u_yf_mail_messages` (which outbound mail was opened)
- **Settings → Cron tasks** — row `LBL_LINK_ACTION_IMPORT` / `Import podpisanych akcji linkowych` (status, last run)
- **Email templates + Template elements** — `candidates_unsubscribe_footer`, `candidates_open_tracking_logo`, variables `LinkActionUrl`, `LinkActionImageUrl`
- **Candidates record** — Maile related list: send status + opened-at time per outbound message; unsubscribe effect: `is_future_contact_allowed` → 0 after import
- **Not in UI:** queue on Cyberfolks, keys/config (files + DB)

## Email

- Token payload includes **`mid`** = `u_yf_mail_messages.id` (signed; not a raw URL id). Open handler requires valid `mid` + outbound row.
- **Send lifecycle** (CRM via `Outbound::sendFromTemplate` / `sendRaw`): `prepare` → parse with `mailMessageId` → enqueue (`sender_ref` + `mail_message_id`) → cron `deliverFromQueueRow` → `sent`|`failed`. Toast on enqueue ≠ SMTP delivered yet (~1 min cron).
- **Open tracking pixel:** template element `candidates_open_tracking_logo` — 1×1 invisible `<img>` via `LinkActionImageUrl`; www serves `assets/pixel.gif` (transparent GIF; URL path still `…/logo.png`). Prefer GIF over PNG — Outlook mishandles PNG alpha.
- **`mailMessageId` absent (preview):** `LinkActionUrl` / `LinkActionImageUrl` emit **deferred** `$(custom : …)$` tokens (not empty `src`/`href`) so compose can round-trip through `contentOverride`.
- **Send with compose preview:** `Vtiger.js` posts editor HTML as `contentOverride` → `Outbound::sendFromTemplate` **re-parses** override after `prepare()` (resolves deferred tokens). Grafts tracking `<img>` from template parse if editor still has stale `src=""`.
- **`TextParser::dynamic()` must copy `mailMessageId`** to the nested parser.
- Variable: `$(custom : LinkActionUrl|unsubscribe|future_contact|email_private)$` — signed click URL for `<a href="…">`.
- Variable: `$(custom : LinkActionImageUrl|open|email|email_private)$` — signed image URL for `<img src="…">`; first load = open in audit log.
- Footer element: `$(dynamic : candidates_unsubscribe_footer)$` (pl_pl / en_us)
- Tracking element: `$(dynamic : candidates_open_tracking_logo)$` (pl_pl / en_us)
- Mass mail guard: `EmailParser::$permissionToSend['Candidates']` → `is_future_contact_allowed`
- **Send / compose preview** (`EmailParser` + record): `dynamic` → inner `custom` resolves on server.
- **Template edit “Podgląd HTML”**: JS `expandDynamicElements` only inlines element HTML — `$(custom : LinkActionUrl…)$` stays literal unless `EmailTemplates` action `ParsePreview` runs (`Edit.js` → `getPreviewDocumentHtmlAsync`). Sample record: latest entity row with non-empty `default_email_field` on `{tablename}cf`.
- `TextParser\Base::__construct` type hint must be `\App\TextParser\TextParser` (not `\App\TextParser` — breaks `VariablePanel` / `getGeneralVariable()`).
- DB in actions: `\App\Db\Db::getInstance()`, not `\App\Db`.
